results.description: Taken in Salima, Malawi, by CDC Medical Officer, Manoj Menon, MD, MPH, this image depicts two children, one proudly holding a bottle of water, and a toy cell phone that he made out of dirt and seeds. Dr. Menon tells, "I was working on a safe water project, interviewing households regarding access to safe drinking water, knowledge, and prevention of diarrheal diseases.  The bottle of water represents one potential option for safe drinking water.  The cell phone revealed his creativity and hope."

The Bong ETU had admitted over 400 patients since it opened in September, 2014.

results.description: This 2013 photograph depicts a bedroom located in a Kumi, Uganda home, wherein, an insecticide-treated bednet had been rolled up above the wood frame bed beneath. When used properly, the bednet would prevent malaria-transmitting mosquitoes from lighting on the skin of potential hosts, in order to obtain their blood meal, and in doing so, transmit the malarial parasite to their sleeping victims.

results.description: "This picture [of a racing camel and its owner], was taken during an Investigation in 2009 in Alkhurma, Saudi Arabia. Alkhurma virus [had been] isolated from patients suffering from hemorrhagic fever", says Pierre Rollin, M.D. "The virus is transmitted by ticks. At the request of the Saudi Ministry of Health, an investigation was done in January, 2010, leading to the launch of the Alkhurma virus national program including surveillance, and development of a diagnostic laboratory."
